cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SOC, cs.CL, cs.DL. 

This paper deals with the persistence of Twitter datasets, which involves issues related to social media, information retrieval, and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing textual content, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
